smg games usually fall into one of these categories:
1. A carefully crafted concept that is intended to be balanced and a close game for all sides.
2. Mindbenders and bamboozlers where the point of the game is for both sides to try to figure out what is going on and make the most of their advantages
3. The werewolf equivalent of using zipties on the bottom of your trousers and chucking 13 ferrets in the top end
This game fits into category 3. As this is not a special, I have ensured everyone *is* special. There are no Vanillas in this game. There are no passive power roles in this game.

Is it balanced? Probably not, it's 13 ferrets in your trousers. Is it fun? Probably not, it's 13 ferrets in your trousers. Will it be amusing for me to spy on? Yes, it's 13 ferrets in someone else's trousers.
